      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "Oscar, I think you&#39;re overstating the case. The first element of a Collection may be arbitrary in a few cases like HashSet, but it is well-defined: it&#39;s .iterator().next(). It&#39;s also <i>stable</i>, in every collection implementation I&#39;ve ever seen.  (related: note that while Set doesn&#39;t guarantee order, every single subtype of Set in the JDK except HashSet does.)"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 10836,
        "reputation" : 199951,
        "user_id" : 20654,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 80,
