    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>There is no such a thing as \"first\" item in a <code>Collection</code> because it is .. well simply a collection. </p>\n\n<p>From the Java doc's <a href=\"http://www.j2ee.me/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Collection.html#iterator()\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Collection.iterator()</a> method:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><em>There are no guarantees concerning the order in which the elements are returned...</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>So you can't.</p>\n\n<p>If you use <strong>another</strong> interface such as <strong>List</strong>, you can do the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String first = strs.get(0);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>But directly from a Collection this is not possible.</p>\n"
