      "body" : "From Comments of the command:  Returns the first element in iterable or defaultValue if the iterable is empty. The Iterators analog to this method is Iterators.getNext(java.util.Iterator&lt;? extends T&gt;, T). If no default value is desired (and the caller instead wants a NoSuchElementException to be thrown), it is recommended that iterable.iterator().next() is used instead. So, no default value needed then use iterable.iterator().next()!"
