    "last_activity_date" : 1644250690,
    "creation_date" : 1644250690,
    "answer_id" : 71021824,
    "question_id" : 1671378,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are using Apache Commons Collections 4 there is an <a href=\"https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-collections/apidocs/org/apache/commons/collections4/IterableUtils.html#first-java.lang.Iterable-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>IterableUtils.first</code></a> method. It contains an optimization in the case of <code>List</code>s and is neat to use. It's very similar to the Guava method. The code would look like</p>\n<pre><code>String firstStr = IterableUtils.first(strs);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
