  "title" : "Java: Get first item from a collection",
  "body" : "<p>If I have a collection, such as <code>Collection&lt;String&gt; strs</code>, how can I get the first item out? I could just call an <code>Iterator</code>, take its first <code>next()</code>, then throw the <code>Iterator</code> away. Is there a less wasteful way to do it?</p>\n"
